Homecoming is next week! Our theme is: "Back to the Future, Jaguar Style."

*Mon. - Clique It Up (Dress like a group in school: jocks, nerds, athlete, organization/club.)

*Tue. - See the Future (Dress like the occupation you want to have in the future.)

*Wed. - As Seen on TV (Dress like your favorite character from a movie or TV show.)

*Thu. - Throwback Thursday (Dress like your favorite decade: 90's, 80's, 70's, etc.)

*Fri. - Spirit (Show your Jaguar Pride.)

These are things that can be found at home. With a little imagination, you'll be dressed to impress! Get your wigs and costumes READY!!!!!

Attention all athletes and parents of athletes: Here is the link for signing up or updating yout DragonFly information for the 20-21 school year.

Students with profiles from last year will need to log in and update his or her information. Students that do not have a profile will need to create one. This needs to be completed by the start of school in order to be eligible to participate in practice and participate in games. This is required for 7-12 grade students planning to participate in Football, Basketball, Baseball, Softball, Cheer, Dance, Band, Archery, Cross Country, Track. If you have issues/questions, contact me at the school, 662-237-4701, or email, nmoncrief@ccsd.ms

Thank you and let's continue to be safe. ~Nathan Moncrief, Athletic Director~

Please read the plan carefully, write down any questions you may have, and call building administrators next week if needed. Please understand we are following MDE recommendations, CDC guidelines, and recommendations from US Education Secretary Betsy DeVos who highly recommends a traditional start to school. The plan may be updated daily, weekly, or monthly as recommendations are made to the school district by MDE and the CDC. All plans are school board approved.

post_text:
We are pleased to inform you that CARROLL COUNTY SCHOOL DISTRICT
will be implementing a new option available to schools participating in the National School Lunch and School Breakfast Programs called the Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) for School Year 2020-2021.

What does this mean for you and your children attending the school(s) identified above?

Great news for you and your students! All enrolled students of CARROLL COUNTY SCHOOL DISTRICT are eligible to receive a healthy breakfast and lunch at school at no charge to your household each day of the 2020-2021 school year. No further action is required of you. Your child(ren) will be able to participate in these meal programs without having to pay a fee or submit an application.

If we can be of any further assistance, please contact Sherri Blaine at 662-237-4444 ext. 5.

This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

Greenwood Leflore Hospital
March 14 at 9:14 PM ¬∑

Today was our first day of this weekend‚Äôs screening centers. We will hold another tomorrow from 9:00 a.m. until 4:00 p.m. for people of concern who have acute illness and/or meet the criteria for COVID-19. Children age 12 and under will be seen in the parking lot of the Greenwood Children‚Äôs Clinic, located at 1405 Strong Avenue. Adults and children above age 13 will be seen in the parking lot of Magnolia Medical Clinic, located at 1413 Strong Avenue. Those who will be seen include people who have the symptoms of fever, coughing, fatigue and difficulty breathing, and have been in close contact with a person known to have COVID-19, or have recently traveled from an area with widespread or ongoing community spread of COVID-19. When you drive up, please do not get out of your vehicle. We will come to you. Here are some photos of just some of the people who helped with today‚Äôs screenings. Thank you to those who are giving up their Saturday and/or Sunday to provide this service for our community.
